# Battle Tested Patterns — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
Cross-language programming patterns extracted from production codebases (React, Linux, Go, Chromium).
Each pattern includes precise GitHub source links, multi-language implementations, and runnable exercises.

## Quality Rules

- Never fabricate source links — leave TODO rather than invent URLs
- Never claim a project uses a pattern without a verifiable GitHub link
- Code must be runnable, not pseudocode
- Multi-language implementations must be idiomatic to each language
- Exercise tests must pass (`pnpm test` / `cargo test` / `go test`)

## Source Link Format
- Must point to `main`/`master` branch or commit SHA
- Must include line numbers: `#L18-L22`
- Must be verified with `curl -I` returning HTTP 200

## Pattern Template
Every pattern must have: One Liner (≤30 words), Core Idea (with diagram), Production Proof (≥2 projects),
Implementation (TS required + ≥1 other language), Exercises (≥2 tests), When to Use, When NOT to Use.

## Tech Stack
- Monorepo: pnpm workspace (docs/, exercises/, playground/)
- Docs: VitePress → GitHub Pages
- Tests: Vitest (TS), cargo test (Rust), go test (Go), pytest (Python)
- Playground: Monaco Editor + Vitest Browser Mode
- Commits: Conventional Commits (feat/fix/docs/ci/chore/test)

## Code Style
- TypeScript: strict mode, no `any`
- Rust: idiomatic, use `#[cfg(test)]` modules
- Go: standard library preferred, table-driven tests
- Python: standard library preferred, type hints, pytest for tests
- Markdown: follow `.markdownlint.json` rules
